26/06/2006
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- President Filip Vujanovic said on Sunday (25 June) that Montenegro and Serbia must be an example of good neighbourly relations, contributing to the well-being of their economies and their citizens.
His Serbian counterpart, Boris Tadic, is visiting Podgorica Monday, the first time a Serbian leader has been there since the dissolution of the former state union last month.
On Friday, Slovenia became the first country to open an embassy in Montenegro.
(RTS, Vijesti - 26/06/06;
Mina - 25/06/06;
Dnevnik, People's Daily - 24/06/06)
